items.name: case badEventEntry
items.desc: An event is missing a required field.

items.name: case badParameterEntry
items.desc: A parameter in an event is missing a required field.

items.name: case engineNotRunning
items.desc: Your app requested haptic playback when the engine wasn’t running.

items.name: case engineStartTimeout
items.desc: The haptic engine timed out while starting.

items.name: case fileNotFound
items.desc: The system couldn’t find an audio file or haptic asset.

items.name: case insufficientPower
items.desc: The operation failed due to power restrictions.

items.name: case invalidAudioResource
items.desc: A pattern dictionary or an event array contain a reference to an invalid audio resource.

items.name: case invalidAudioSession
items.desc: The system invalidated the audio session associated with the haptic engine.

items.name: case invalidEngineParameter
items.desc: Your app attempted to initialize the haptic engine with an invalid configuration parameter.

items.name: case invalidEventDuration
items.desc: An event in the dictionary has an invalid duration.

items.name: case invalidEventTime
items.desc: The time of an event in the dictionary is invalid.

items.name: case invalidEventType
items.desc: The type of an event in the dictionary is invalid.

items.name: case invalidParameterType
items.desc: A pattern dictionary or parameter array contains an unknown or invalid parameter type.

items.name: case invalidPatternData
items.desc: Your app passed an invalid pattern to the haptic engine or player.

items.name: case invalidPatternDictionary
items.desc: A pattern in the dictionary is missing a required field.

items.name: case invalidPatternPlayer
items.desc: The current pattern player is no longer valid due to a server error.

items.name: case invalidTime
items.desc: The time offset passed to the haptic engine is invalid.

items.name: case memoryError
items.desc: The operation failed due to a lack of memory.

items.name: case notSupported
items.desc: The current device doesn’t support the haptic engine.

items.name: case operationNotPermitted
items.desc: Your app requested an operation that the haptic engine disallows.

items.name: case resourceNotAvailable
items.desc: The framework didn’t locate a named resource.

items.name: case serverInterrupted
items.desc: Your app lost its connection to the haptic server.

items.name: case serverInitFailed
items.desc: The haptic server failed to initialize.

items.name: case unknownError
items.desc: An operation failed due to an unknown error.
